# TypeScript-STL
##### Finally, TypeScript-STL v1.0 is approaching.

Most of Standard Template Libraries are implemented. Throughing tests and feedbacks for few months, TypeScript-STL will be published as v1.0.
##### Refatored for preparing Collection.

The future's **Collection** library, observes elements I/O. You can detect inserted and deleted elements by using `callback function` or `addEventListener` function. Those **Collection** containers will be implemented by inheriting containers in this **TypeScript-STL**.

The **Collection containers** may be named such like:
- ICollection -> implements std.base.IContainer, samchon.library.IEventDispatcher
- Linear Collections
  - ArrayCollection -> extends std.Vector
  - ListCollection -> extends std.List
  - DequeCollection -> extends std.Deque
- Hash & Tree Collections
  - HashSetCollection -> extends std.HashSet
  - HashMapCollection -> extends std.HashMap
  - TreeSetCollection -> extends std.TreeSet
  - TreeMapCollection -> extends std.TreeMap
- XMLListCollection
  - extends samchon.library.XMLList 
  - implements ICollection

The **Container** library will be realized in **Samchon Framework**.
- `namespace samchon.collection`
- Samchon Framework: https://github.com/samchon/framework
##### Fix errors on sequence specified ordering in tree containers.
- Wrong sequence ordering doesn't be occured.
- Inserting an element with hint works correctly.
#### Reverse iterators are separated from formal iterators.

Derived (non-basic) iterators do not inherit formal iterators. It will enhance type checking and prevent mistakes using reverse and formal iterators, in some functions getting range iterators, at the same time.
###### Reverse iterator do not extends formal iterator

``` java
// ORDINARY REVERSE_ITERATOR
class VectorReverseIterator<T> 
    extends VectorIterator<T> 
    implements base.IReverseIterator<T>;

// NEWELY UPDATED REVERSE_ITERATOR
class VectorReverseIterator<T>
    extends ReverseIterator<VectorIterator<T>>
```
###### Enhanced Type Checks

``` java
let vector: std.Vector<number> = new std.Vector<number(5, 1);
vector.erase(vector.begin(), vector.rend()); 
    // Invalid range iterators, formal and reverse iterators are used at the same time
    // IT CAUSES COMPILE ERROR FROM NOW ON
```
##### API Documents are enhanced.

Comments for API documents generation on basic objects are on fill.
- http://samchon.github.io/stl/api
##### Class Diagram is re-designed.

Class Diagram represents the **TypeScript-STL** is re-designed and published.
- http://samchon.github.io/stl/design/class_diagram.pdf

---
# Samchon-Framework

A SDN framework who can integrate C++ server and TypeScript clients and implement distributed processing system. Realizing distributed system is only possible in C++ and Node is not supported yet, but soon.
### Documents
- API Documents
  - C++: http://samchon.github.io/framework/api/cpp
  - TypeScript: http://samchon.io/samchon/framework/api/ts
  - Flex: http://samchon.github.io/framework/api/flex
- Architecture Designs
  - C++ Class Diagram: http://samchon.github.io/framework/design/cpp_class_diagram.pdf
  - JS Class Diagram: http://samchon.github.io/framework/design/js_class_diagram.pdf
  - Conception Diagram: http://samchon.github.io/framework/design/conception_diagram.pdf
  - ERD: http://samchon.github.io/framework/design/entity_relationship_diagram.pdf
  - Sequence Diagram: http://samchon.github.io/framework/design/sequence_diagram.pdf
- Development Guide: http://samchon.github.io/framework/doc/development_guide.pdf
### Sub-modules
##### Samchon-Library

A common libraries for Samchon Framework

XML, StringUtil and Event libraries are implemented.
##### Samchon-Collection

A extended STL containers who can detect elements I/O.

The element I/O will be dispatched as an event or by callback function.

title: The click event handler for the title action of Infobox entities need…
body: Because the Infobox title click handler is attached to an anchor tag with a hash as its destination (<a href="#">), the hash can cause problems in frameworks like Angular when used in conjunction with a <base href="/"> tag. title: [RFC] Lodash flow better arguments
body:
I've tried to implement some overloads for `_.flow` function.
There is no unit tests, and no overloads for lodash object wrappers.
Mainly, I want you to give me a feedback about this. If it is acceptable, I'll add more overloads and write the tests.

The main reason to make thie change is to have a better type inferring:

``` typescript
import flow from "lodash/flow"

declare function f1(a: number): boolean;
declare function f2(a: boolean): string;
declare function f3(a: string): DOMElement;

let pipeline = _.flow(f1, f2, f3); // pipeline now have inferred type (a: number) => DOMElement
```

https://lodash.com/docs#flow

P.S. writing similar overloads is common case for Scala.

title: Typing Location.Query to K,V dictionary
body:
case 1. Add a new type definition.
- [x] checked compilation succeeds with `--target es6` and `--noImplicitAny` options.
- [x] has correct [naming convention](http://definitelytyped.org/guides/contributing.html#naming-the-file)
- [x] has a [test file](http://definitelytyped.org/guides/contributing.html#tests) with the suffix of  `-tests.ts` or `-tests.tsx`.

case 2. Improvement to existing type definition.
- documentation or source code reference which provides context for the suggested changes.  url http://api.jquery.com/html .
  - it has been reviewed by a DefinitelyTyped member.

Location.Query is actually typed as 'Object', which forces to cast it to 'any' anytime you need to access one of your own query string parameter.

```
const clientId = (this.props.location.query as any).clientId;
```

It should be typed as '{ [key: string]: string; }' since it's a dictionary where you can get your arbitrary named query string parameters.
